<div class="relative isolate overflow-hidden">
  <%= render 'top_links' %>
  <div class="absolute left-[calc(50%-4rem)] top-10 -z-10 transform-gpu blur-3xl sm:left-[calc(50%-18rem)] lg:left-48 lg:top-[calc(50%-30rem)] xl:left-[calc(50%-24rem)]" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="aspect-1108/632 w-[69.25rem] bg-linear-to-r from-[#80caff] to-[#4f46e5] opacity-20" style="clip-path: polygon(73.6% 51.7%, 91.7% 11.8%, 100% 46.4%, 97.4% 82.2%, 92.5% 84.9%, 75.7% 64%, 55.3% 47.5%, 46.5% 49.4%, 45% 62.9%, 50.3% 87.2%, 21.3% 64.1%, 0.1% 100%, 5.4% 51.1%, 21.4% 63.9%, 58.9% 0.2%, 73.6% 51.7%)"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 pb-16 pt-8 sm:pb-16 lg:px-8 lg:pt-40 flex flex-col">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-x-6 ml-8 mb-8">
      <%= image_tag 'logo-small.png', class: 'h-16 w-auto', alt: "Logo for the 'Tool for Systemic Change'" %>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-6xl">Takedown Policy</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="text-white bg-teal-900 rounded-lg p-8 w-full">
      <h2 class="text-3x1 font-bold leading-10">Purpose</h2>
      <p class="my-4 text-gray-300">        
        This policy outlines the procedures for handling requests to remove or restrict access to content 
        hosted on our platform. We are committed to complying with Australian laws, including copyright, 
        privacy, and defamation legislation, while balancing the principles of freedom of expression and 
        equitable access to information.
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-3x1 font-bold leading-10">Scope</h2>
      <p class="my-4 text-gray-300">        
        This policy applies to all content hosted on our platform, including user-generated content and 
        materials provided by third parties.
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-3x1 font-bold leading-10">Grounds for Takedown</h2>
      <p class="my-4 text-gray-300">        
        Content may be subject to takedown or access restrictions under the following circumstances:
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4">
          <li>Breach of copyright laws, as outlined in the Australian Copyright Act 1968.</li>
          <li>Violation of privacy laws, including the Privacy Act 1988.</li>
          <li>Defamatory content, as defined under Australian defamation laws.</li>
          <li>
            Content deemed objectionable or harmful under Australian law, such as material that incites 
            violence or hate speech.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-3x1 font-bold leading-10">Procedure for Takedown Requests</h2>
      <p class="my-4 text-gray-300">        
        <span class="bold">1.	Submission:</span> Requests must be submitted in writing via our 
          <%= landing_pages_link_to 'designated contact form', takedown_contacts_path %> or email. The 
          request should include:
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4">
          <li>
            Identification of the content in question (<span class="italic">e.g.</span> URL or description).
          </li>
          <li>Reason for the takedown request, citing relevant legal grounds.</li>
          <li>Contact information of the requestor.</li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <p class="my-4 text-gray-300">        
        <span class="bold">2.	Review:</span> Upon receiving a request, we will:
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4">
          <li>Verify the validity of the claim.</li>
          <li>Assess the content against applicable laws and our terms of service.</li>
        </ul>
      </p>

      <p class="my-4 text-gray-300">        
        <span class="bold">3.	Action:</span> If the request is deemed valid:
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4">
          <li>The content will be removed or access restricted promptly.</li>
          <li>The affected user will be notified and given an opportunity to contest the decision.</li>
        </ul>
      </p>

      <p class="my-4 text-gray-300">        
        <span class="bold">4.	Appeals:</span> Users may appeal takedown decisions by providing additional 
        information or evidence supporting their case.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3x1 font-bold leading-10">Transparency</h2>
      <p class="my-4 text-gray-300">        
        We will maintain a public record of takedown requests, excluding sensitive information, to ensure 
        transparency and accountability.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3x1 font-bold leading-10">Periodic Review</h2>
      <p class="my-4 text-gray-300">        
        Content that has been removed or restricted will be periodically reviewed to determine whether it can 
        be reinstated.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-3x1 font-bold leading-10">Contact Us</h2>
      <p class="my-4 text-gray-300">        
        For takedown requests, please contact us at 
        <%= landing_pages_link_to 'takedown@toolforsystemicchange.com', 'mailto:takedown@toolforsystemicchange.com' %> 
        or via the <%= landing_pages_link_to 'Takedown Request Form', takedown_contacts_path %>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>